The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Insurer fined
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Insurer fined
                            
	Hyderabad, Aug. 7 (PTI): The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority has imposed a fine of Rs 10 lakh on life insurer SBI Life for deviating from an offer document in one of its schemes.        
	 The insurer has been asked to pay Rs 10 lakh within 30 days from the date of receipt of the order.        
	One clause denied the payment of death claim in the event of death within 45 days from the commencement of the policy. The other clause provisioned for rejecting the payment of death claim on intimation within 90 days after death, the order said.                                                                                                                                                          
